    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-27T08:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-27T08:35:00-05:00" n="669"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d669">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363/810: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-27T17:00:00+03:25"
                            >November 27, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 4—3:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1070. Prime Minister told me yesterday that British Minister had informed him two
                    British oil representatives were already here to negotiate for Baluchistan
                    concession (my 1065, November 15, and Department’s 584, November 23) on same
                    terms as those of old Amiranian Oil Company concession.<note n="46"
                        xml:id="d669fn46">The Amiranian Oil Company of New York; see <ref
                            target="frus1937v02#pg_734">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1937, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, pp. 734</ref>.</note> I told Soheily that
                    I had communicated with Department and I thought American oil company
                    representatives might be expected soon. He expressed pleasure and repeated his
                    interest in having concession go to America.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
